column121: Symptomatic children will be kept in an isolation room until picked up by parent/guardian. Parents/guardians of students in close proximity to a COVID-19 positive person will be notified in writing. Such students will need to receive a negative test for COVID-19 or may return to school only at the conclusion of a 14-day asymptomatic self-quarantine or when all three of the following criteria are met: at least three days (72 hours) have passed since recovery (resolution of fever without the use of fever-reducing medications); the individual has improvement in symptoms (e.g., cough, shortness of breath); and at least ten days have passed since symptoms first appeared.  In the case of an individual who has symptoms that could be COVID-19 and who is not evaluated by a medical professional or tested for COVID-19, such individual is assumed to have COVID-19, and the individual may not return to the campus until the individual has completed the same three-step set of criteria listed above.
